    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Add these two properties to your parent layout (ex: Linear Layout, Relative Layout)</p>\n\n<pre><code>android:focusable=\"false\"\nandroid:focusableInTouchMode=\"false\" \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It will do the trick :)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5111027,
      "reputation" : 3088,
      "user_id" : 4097592,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-RzHlkfPbsfg/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAIg/7UkZy_yCbxg/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Dayanand Waghmare",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4097592/dayanand-waghmare"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1452091705,
    "creation_date" : 1452091705,
    "answer_id" : 34635955,
    "question_id" : 9732761,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just Add in AndroidManifest.xml</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;activity android:name=\".HomeActivity\"  android:windowSoftInputMode=\"stateHidden\"&gt;\n&lt;/activity&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3804767,
      "reputation" : 431,
      "user_id" : 3157498,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/100007157857592/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Efe &#214;ZYER",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3157498/efe-%c3%96zyer"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1470383946,
    "creation_date" : 1470383946,
    "answer_id" : 38784111,
    "question_id" : 9732761,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Best solution for me, paste your class </p>\n\n<pre><code>@Override\npublic void onResume() {\n    this.getWindow().setSoftInputMode(WindowManager.LayoutParams.SOFT_INPUT_STATE_ALWAYS_HIDDEN);\n    super.onResume();\n}\n\n@Override\npublic void onStart() {\n    this.getWindow().setSoftInputMode(WindowManager.LayoutParams.SOFT_INPUT_STATE_ALWAYS_HIDDEN);\n    super.onStart();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 13227065,
      "reputation" : 345,
      "user_id" : 9551861,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/baeb17737067ee973dd587c8abd6c24b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Jack T",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9551861/jack-t"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1575027141,
    "last_edit_date" : 1575027141,
    "creation_date" : 1523973444,
    "answer_id" : 49880101,
    "question_id" : 9732761,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can also write these lines of code in the <strong>direct</strong> parent layout of the .xml layout file in which you have the \"problem\":</p>\n\n<pre><code>android:focusable=\"true\"\nandroid:focusableInTouchMode=\"true\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?&gt;\n&lt;LinearLayout xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n    android:layout_width=\"match_parent\"\n    ...\n    android:focusable=\"true\"\n    android:focusableInTouchMode=\"true\" &gt;\n\n    &lt;EditText\n        android:id=\"@+id/myEditText\"\n        ...\n        android:hint=\"@string/write_here\" /&gt;\n\n    &lt;Button\n        android:id=\"@+id/button_ok\"\n        ...\n        android:text=\"@string/ok\" /&gt;\n&lt;/LinearLayout&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><br>\n<strong>EDIT :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Example if the EditText is contained in another layout:</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?&gt;\n&lt;ConstraintLayout xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n    android:layout_width=\"match_parent\"\n    ... &gt;                                            &lt;!--not here--&gt;\n\n    ...    &lt;!--other elements--&gt;\n\n    &lt;LinearLayout\n        android:id=\"@+id/theDirectParent\"\n        ...\n        android:focusable=\"true\"\n        android:focusableInTouchMode=\"true\" &gt;        &lt;!--here--&gt;\n\n        &lt;EditText\n            android:id=\"@+id/myEditText\"\n            ...\n            android:hint=\"@string/write_here\" /&gt;\n\n        &lt;Button\n            android:id=\"@+id/button_ok\"\n            ...\n            android:text=\"@string/ok\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/LinearLayout&gt;\n\n&lt;/ConstraintLayout&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The key is to make sure that the EditText is not directly focusable. <br>\nBye! ;-)</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 442556,
      "reputation" : 3273,
      "user_id" : 833219,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 61,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e7df0bfe7b6a4eadf8b58488ecc0764c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "haythem souissi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/833219/haythem-souissi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1524238778,
    "creation_date" : 1524238778,
    "answer_id" : 49945282,
    "question_id" : 9732761,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>just add this on your Activity:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Override\npublic boolean dispatchTouchEvent(MotionEvent ev) {\n      if (getCurrentFocus() != null) {\n           InputMethodManager imm = (InputMethodManager) getSystemService(Context.INPUT_METHOD_SERVICE);\n           imm.hideSoftInputFromWindow(getCurrentFocus().getWindowToken(), 0);\n      }\n      return super.dispatchTouchEvent(ev);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3034759,
      "reputation" : 581,
      "user_id" : 2573109,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/8RBj2.jpg?s=256",
